Text.SourceString: I couldn't sleep last night so I went out to our porch.//<portrait=normal>I just saw the most breathtaking meteor shower last night. Wish you were there to witness it with me.
Text.LocalizedString: I couldn't sleep last night so I went out to our porch.//<portrait=normal>I just saw the most breathtaking meteor shower last night. Wish you were there to witness it with me.

Text.SourceString: I've been reminiscing about our early days, when we used to hangout together around town.//<portrait=blushing>I remember being so nervous around you sometimes. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I've been reminiscing about our early days, when we used to hangout together around town.//<portrait=blushing>I remember being so nervous around you sometimes. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: Those memories still bring a smile to my face.
Text.LocalizedString: Those memories still bring a smile to my face.

Text.SourceString: I had a dream last night that we were floating among the galaxies, hand in hand.
Text.LocalizedString: I had a dream last night that we were floating among the galaxies, hand in hand.

Text.SourceString: It reminded me how lucky I am to have you by my side, both on Earth and in the vastness of the universe.
Text.LocalizedString: It reminded me how lucky I am to have you by my side, both on Earth and in the vastness of the universe.

Text.SourceString: Good morning, hon! Did you sleep well?
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, hon! Did you sleep well?

Text.SourceString: Hon, have you seen my lucky pen? I can't seem to find it anywhere.
Text.LocalizedString: Hon, have you seen my lucky pen? I can't seem to find it anywhere.

Text.SourceString: Maybe it's at Mama's house.//I'll go check there.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe it's at Mama's house.//I'll go check there.

Text.SourceString: Being the oldest sibling, I've always had to lead the way.//<portrait=happy>But here on the farm, we're a team. I like it.
Text.LocalizedString: Being the oldest sibling, I've always had to lead the way.//<portrait=happy>But here on the farm, we're a team. I like it.

Text.SourceString: Just finished some calculations for the new rocket propulsion system.//I'd love to talk about it with you over dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: Just finished some calculations for the new rocket propulsion system.//I'd love to talk about it with you over dinner.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes <NpcName>Frank</> pulls pranks on me. You're officially in the family now, so you're fair game too!//<portrait=happy>Watch your back... and your boots!
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes <NpcName>Frank</> pulls pranks on me. You're officially in the family now, so you're fair game too!//<portrait=happy>Watch your back... and your boots!

Text.SourceString: Good morning, my stellar spouse!//Do you like that pet name?
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, my stellar spouse!//Do you like that pet name?

Text.SourceString: honestly never thought I’d ever get married. Yet here we are.//Like two peas in a pod.
Text.LocalizedString: honestly never thought I’d ever get married. Yet here we are.//Like two peas in a pod.

Text.SourceString: Some folks said I'd marry my job.//Guess what? We showed them I could do one better!
Text.LocalizedString: Some folks said I'd marry my job.//Guess what? We showed them I could do one better!

Text.SourceString: Give me a shout if you need help, okay honey? I may not know much about farming, but I'm a fast learner.
Text.LocalizedString: Give me a shout if you need help, okay honey? I may not know much about farming, but I'm a fast learner.

Text.SourceString: Busy with Spring plantings, I see. Remember, the universe wasn't created in a day.//Take your time, honey!
Text.LocalizedString: Busy with Spring plantings, I see. Remember, the universe wasn't created in a day.//Take your time, honey!

Text.SourceString: Can't wait to see all the fruits you’ll be growing this Summer!//I bet those fruits are gonna be out of this world.
Text.LocalizedString: Can't wait to see all the fruits you’ll be growing this Summer!//I bet those fruits are gonna be out of this world.

Text.SourceString: Honey, you’re growing strawberries this season, right?//You know it’s one of my favorites.
Text.LocalizedString: Honey, you’re growing strawberries this season, right?//You know it’s one of my favorites.

Text.SourceString: Take it easy today, honey.//I worry about you.
Text.LocalizedString: Take it easy today, honey.//I worry about you.

Text.SourceString: Honey, you’re growing coffee beans this season, right?//You know it’s one of my favorites.
Text.LocalizedString: Honey, you’re growing coffee beans this season, right?//You know it’s one of my favorites.

Text.SourceString: Have you found any white hibiscus yet?//There should be plenty this season but I haven’t been able to find any.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you found any white hibiscus yet?//There should be plenty this season but I haven’t been able to find any.

Text.SourceString: I'm on a mission to make our place smell like Fall... and mooncakes!//Because Mama said, nothing says 'autumn' like lunar pastries.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm on a mission to make our place smell like Fall... and mooncakes!//Because Mama said, nothing says 'autumn' like lunar pastries.

Text.SourceString: Crisp air, changing leaves, and space-worthy pumpkin pie.//<portrait=normal>You know, hon, Fall on the farm might just beat Fall in space!
Text.LocalizedString: Crisp air, changing leaves, and space-worthy pumpkin pie.//<portrait=normal>You know, hon, Fall on the farm might just beat Fall in space!

Text.SourceString: You've got to be careful with those falling leaves.//One of them once hid a snake and gave Mama a jump scare!
Text.LocalizedString: You've got to be careful with those falling leaves.//One of them once hid a snake and gave Mama a jump scare!

Text.SourceString: Mama usually goes all out baking mooncakes around this time of the year.//Think I'll swing by her place this week with some.
Text.LocalizedString: Mama usually goes all out baking mooncakes around this time of the year.//Think I'll swing by her place this week with some.

Text.SourceString: Good excuse to check in and see how she's doing.
Text.LocalizedString: Good excuse to check in and see how she's doing.

Text.SourceString: I love you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I love you, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I love you, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I love you so <Italic>so</> much.
Text.LocalizedString: I love you, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I love you so <Italic>so</> much.

Text.SourceString: I like how you make sure to kiss me every night.
Text.LocalizedString: I like how you make sure to kiss me every night.

Text.SourceString: You know how to make me feel loved.
Text.LocalizedString: You know how to make me feel loved.

Text.SourceString: Honey, thank you for always having my back.//And just so you know, I've got yours too.
Text.LocalizedString: Honey, thank you for always having my back.//And just so you know, I've got yours too.

Text.SourceString: I've been thinking about Dad lately.
Text.LocalizedString: I've been thinking about Dad lately.

Text.SourceString: I miss him.
Text.LocalizedString: I miss him.

Text.SourceString: Be careful out there, okay? The ice is going to be slippery.
Text.LocalizedString: Be careful out there, okay? The ice is going to be slippery.

Text.SourceString: With these clear Winter skies, we could probably spot The Space Station.
Text.LocalizedString: With these clear Winter skies, we could probably spot The Space Station.

Text.SourceString: Up on the space station, I used to miss the scent of rain. There's nothing like it, really.
Text.LocalizedString: Up on the space station, I used to miss the scent of rain. There's nothing like it, really.

Text.SourceString: Living here with you, it's the first time in forever that I haven't had to share my space with a small crowd.
Text.LocalizedString: Living here with you, it's the first time in forever that I haven't had to share my space with a small crowd.

Text.SourceString: No brothers, no academy roommates, just us.
Text.LocalizedString: No brothers, no academy roommates, just us.

Text.SourceString: I worry about Mama being alone sometimes.//But <NPCName>Noah</> is still around, right? Plus, we can pop in for a visit whenever.
Text.LocalizedString: I worry about Mama being alone sometimes.//But <NPCName>Noah</> is still around, right? Plus, we can pop in for a visit whenever.

Text.SourceString: Feels really good to be back here.
Text.LocalizedString: Feels really good to be back here.

Text.SourceString: My old room is still intact! Looks like <NpcName>Noah</> hasn't turned it into a storage yet.
Text.LocalizedString: My old room is still intact! Looks like <NpcName>Noah</> hasn't turned it into a storage yet.

Text.SourceString: Gotta clean this.//Looks like I'll be battling this stubborn stain for awhile.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta clean this.//Looks like I'll be battling this stubborn stain for awhile.

Text.SourceString: I'll be back a little later than usual today, honey.//I need to help my brothers close up.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll be back a little later than usual today, honey.//I need to help my brothers close up.

Text.SourceString: Hey honey, if you need anything. Just let <NPCName>Frank</> know.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey honey, if you need anything. Just let <NPCName>Frank</> know.

Text.SourceString: Oh, hey there, love! Fancy running into you here.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, hey there, love! Fancy running into you here.

Text.SourceString: Are you looking for me?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you looking for me?

Text.SourceString: Are you here to check in on Mama too?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you here to check in on Mama too?

Text.SourceString: I might need to come back here tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I might need to come back here tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: I need to get some books from my room.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to get some books from my room.

Text.SourceString: Planning to go to the Cherry Blossom Festival, <PlayerName>$player</>?//My family's gonna be there. I don’t want to miss it!
Text.LocalizedString: Planning to go to the Cherry Blossom Festival, <PlayerName>$player</>?//My family's gonna be there. I don’t want to miss it!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Frank</> will be manning the grill again this year.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Frank</> will be manning the grill again this year.

Text.SourceString: Did you enjoy the Cherry Blossom Festival yesterday, honey?//<portrait=normal>I ate so much I could hardly walk home!
Text.LocalizedString: Did you enjoy the Cherry Blossom Festival yesterday, honey?//<portrait=normal>I ate so much I could hardly walk home!

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind the cold weather and stuff, but nothing, and I mean, <Italic>nothing</> beats eating outdoors.//But it’s much better in Spring than in the middle of an ice-cold Winter afternoon, of course.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind the cold weather and stuff, but nothing, and I mean, <Italic>nothing</> beats eating outdoors.//But it’s much better in Spring than in the middle of an ice-cold Winter afternoon, of course.

Text.SourceString: Enjoying Spring so far, hon?
Text.LocalizedString: Enjoying Spring so far, hon?

Text.SourceString: Are you going to <NPCName>Bree’s</> for the New Year’s feast, honey?//Maybe we can go together. It’s going to be a good time!
Text.LocalizedString: Are you going to <NPCName>Bree’s</> for the New Year’s feast, honey?//Maybe we can go together. It’s going to be a good time!

Text.SourceString: My brothers and I used to build snow forts in weather like this.//Our snowball wars were epic!
Text.LocalizedString: My brothers and I used to build snow forts in weather like this.//Our snowball wars were epic!

Text.SourceString: Now that I’m home, I don’t get to fly as much… I miss it.
Text.LocalizedString: Now that I’m home, I don’t get to fly as much… I miss it.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Chaem</> is fun to play volleyball with. She’s really good.//Learning a lot of tricks and stuff from her.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Chaem</> is fun to play volleyball with. She’s really good.//Learning a lot of tricks and stuff from her.

Text.SourceString: When I was in basic training, they made us camp out for three days in weather like this.//A test of endurance and your ability to stay cooped up in a small space with a bunch of people.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was in basic training, they made us camp out for three days in weather like this.//A test of endurance and your ability to stay cooped up in a small space with a bunch of people.

Text.SourceString: When I was in basic training, they made us camp out for three days in weather like this.//A test of endurance and your ability to stay cooped up in a small space with a bunch of people.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was in basic training, they made us camp out for three days in weather like this.//A test of endurance and your ability to stay cooped up in a small space with a bunch of people.

Text.SourceString: When I was in basic training, they made us camp out for three days in weather like this.//A test of endurance and your ability to stay cooped up in a small space with a bunch of people.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was in basic training, they made us camp out for three days in weather like this.//A test of endurance and your ability to stay cooped up in a small space with a bunch of people.

Text.SourceString: When I was in basic training, they made us camp out for three days in weather like this.//A test of endurance and your ability to stay cooped up in a small space with a bunch of people.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was in basic training, they made us camp out for three days in weather like this.//A test of endurance and your ability to stay cooped up in a small space with a bunch of people.

Text.SourceString: When I was in basic training, they made us camp out for three days in weather like this.//A test of endurance and your ability to stay cooped up in a small space with a bunch of people.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was in basic training, they made us camp out for three days in weather like this.//A test of endurance and your ability to stay cooped up in a small space with a bunch of people.

Text.SourceString: The rain is intense. I hope our farm is okay.
Text.LocalizedString: The rain is intense. I hope our farm is okay.

Text.SourceString: You know what I’m craving right now, <PlayerName>$player</>? A nice hot cup of coffee…//I’m gonna go and get some.
Text.LocalizedString: You know what I’m craving right now, <PlayerName>$player</>? A nice hot cup of coffee…//I’m gonna go and get some.

Text.SourceString: You know what I’m craving right now, <PlayerName>$player</>? A nice, hot cup of coffee…//I’m gonna go and get some.
Text.LocalizedString: You know what I’m craving right now, <PlayerName>$player</>? A nice, hot cup of coffee…//I’m gonna go and get some.

Text.SourceString: The storm is intense. I hope our farm is okay.
Text.LocalizedString: The storm is intense. I hope our farm is okay.

Text.SourceString: I hope it doesn't flood at the tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it doesn't flood at the tavern.

Text.SourceString: You know, I’m glad to be back on Coral Island, but it’s not quite the same without my dad and my little brother here.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, I’m glad to be back on Coral Island, but it’s not quite the same without my dad and my little brother here.

Text.SourceString: Do you have more layers you can wear?//<portrait=normal>Winter is next week, and it seems like it might be a cold one this year.//I don't want you to get sick, honey.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have more layers you can wear?//<portrait=normal>Winter is next week, and it seems like it might be a cold one this year.//I don't want you to get sick, honey.

Text.SourceString: I’m A-OK to spend my whole Summer at the beach, playing volleyball.//But the thing is, I can’t seem to find any partners other than <NPCName>Chaem</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m A-OK to spend my whole Summer at the beach, playing volleyball.//But the thing is, I can’t seem to find any partners other than <NPCName>Chaem</>.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, <NPCName>Paul</> is there sometimes and stuff. Just not often enough, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, <NPCName>Paul</> is there sometimes and stuff. Just not often enough, you know?

Text.SourceString: I can’t imagine going to the hot spring in this heat.//But I heard from my friend <NPCName>Chaem</> that the hunter dude goes there in Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t imagine going to the hot spring in this heat.//But I heard from my friend <NPCName>Chaem</> that the hunter dude goes there in Summer.

Text.SourceString: Playing volleyball with <NPCName>Chaem</> pushes me to be a better player… I like it.//It makes me better, <Italic>and</> I get to work out.
Text.LocalizedString: Playing volleyball with <NPCName>Chaem</> pushes me to be a better player… I like it.//It makes me better, <Italic>and</> I get to work out.

Text.SourceString: Besides, she told me she needed a partner to train with.//<portrait=normal>I mean, if I can be of help, why not, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Besides, she told me she needed a partner to train with.//<portrait=normal>I mean, if I can be of help, why not, right?

Text.SourceString: Every several weeks or so, <NPCName>Eddy</> does his disappearing act where he doesn’t answer mail and makes Mama all worried.
Text.LocalizedString: Every several weeks or so, <NPCName>Eddy</> does his disappearing act where he doesn’t answer mail and makes Mama all worried.

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna have to snoop on social media and find out what he’s up to.//<portrait=angry>He’s got me all worried too!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna have to snoop on social media and find out what he’s up to.//<portrait=angry>He’s got me all worried too!

Text.SourceString: Being outdoors on a warm Spring day like this is my favorite.//Get that vitamin D, move your body… When your mind is clear, your day will be too.
Text.LocalizedString: Being outdoors on a warm Spring day like this is my favorite.//Get that vitamin D, move your body… When your mind is clear, your day will be too.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad to be where I am in life, but I can’t stop here, no. I wanna keep educating myself…reach for the stars, as it were.//<portrait=normal>I gotta set a good example for my little brothers.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad to be where I am in life, but I can’t stop here, no. I wanna keep educating myself…reach for the stars, as it were.//<portrait=normal>I gotta set a good example for my little brothers.

Text.SourceString: The weekend’s here. I’m gonna get <NPCName>Noah</> to play volleyball with me tomorrow, hon.//<portrait=annoyed>He’s probably gonna say no again. It’s hard to get that one to do any sports.
Text.LocalizedString: The weekend’s here. I’m gonna get <NPCName>Noah</> to play volleyball with me tomorrow, hon.//<portrait=annoyed>He’s probably gonna say no again. It’s hard to get that one to do any sports.

Text.SourceString: You’re one reliable farmer, honey.//I like that trait in a person.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re one reliable farmer, honey.//I like that trait in a person.

Text.SourceString: Gah! I got sand in my mouth!
Text.LocalizedString: Gah! I got sand in my mouth!

Text.SourceString: The beach is nice this time of year.//<portrait=happy>Well, the beach is nice <Italic>any</> time of year, to be honest. Especially when the weather is perfect like this.
Text.LocalizedString: The beach is nice this time of year.//<portrait=happy>Well, the beach is nice <Italic>any</> time of year, to be honest. Especially when the weather is perfect like this.

Text.SourceString: It brings back a lot of childhood memories.
Text.LocalizedString: It brings back a lot of childhood memories.

Text.SourceString: That volleyball thing over there…it’s been here since I was little.//But the bright-red color is new.
Text.LocalizedString: That volleyball thing over there…it’s been here since I was little.//But the bright-red color is new.

Text.SourceString: The whole area, including the chair, used to be blue.
Text.LocalizedString: The whole area, including the chair, used to be blue.

Text.SourceString: Going on a walk, honey?//I’m gonna have to wash my hair tonight… The smell of the ocean is strong today.
Text.LocalizedString: Going on a walk, honey?//I’m gonna have to wash my hair tonight… The smell of the ocean is strong today.

Text.SourceString: I like getting coffee at <NPCName>Raj’s</> place.//They’re good at making coffee – my favorite!
Text.LocalizedString: I like getting coffee at <NPCName>Raj’s</> place.//They’re good at making coffee – my favorite!

Text.SourceString: They once told me about how every cup is special – creating one is a work of art, things like that.//<portrait=happy>It works, though! Because the coffee at their place just tastes better than it does at home. I don’t know how to describe it.
Text.LocalizedString: They once told me about how every cup is special – creating one is a work of art, things like that.//<portrait=happy>It works, though! Because the coffee at their place just tastes better than it does at home. I don’t know how to describe it.

Text.SourceString: Don’t let the heat get you, honey!//Power through!
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t let the heat get you, honey!//Power through!

Text.SourceString: You look like you’re ready for Summer, hon. Good for you.
Text.LocalizedString: You look like you’re ready for Summer, hon. Good for you.

Text.SourceString: Thankfully I’ve fixed Fishensips’ ventilation just in time for Summer. It turned out there were clumped-up leaves stuck in there.//<portrait=annoyed>Gah!
Text.LocalizedString: Thankfully I’ve fixed Fishensips’ ventilation just in time for Summer. It turned out there were clumped-up leaves stuck in there.//<portrait=annoyed>Gah!

Text.SourceString: Could’ve been worse, I guess… It could’ve been a dead rat or worse…
Text.LocalizedString: Could’ve been worse, I guess… It could’ve been a dead rat or worse…

Text.SourceString: The grass changes color in Summer. Did you notice that?
Text.LocalizedString: The grass changes color in Summer. Did you notice that?

Text.SourceString: Winter is nice here, at the farm. I like the snow in the trees.//<portrait=annoyed>Only in trees! When there’s snow on the path – that’s different.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter is nice here, at the farm. I like the snow in the trees.//<portrait=annoyed>Only in trees! When there’s snow on the path – that’s different.

Text.SourceString: At the rate it’s been snowing, We'll be out shoveling every day starting tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: At the rate it’s been snowing, We'll be out shoveling every day starting tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: At the rate it’s been snowing, We'll be out shoveling every day starting tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: At the rate it’s been snowing, We'll be out shoveling every day starting tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: At the rate it’s been snowing, We'll be out shoveling every day starting tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: At the rate it’s been snowing, We'll be out shoveling every day starting tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: At the rate it’s been snowing, We'll be out shoveling every day starting tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: At the rate it’s been snowing, We'll be out shoveling every day starting tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Do you think you might enter the crop display contest at the Harvest Festival?//<portrait=surprised>You should! You might win something!
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think you might enter the crop display contest at the Harvest Festival?//<portrait=surprised>You should! You might win something!

Text.SourceString: Saw <NpcName>Lily</> cleaning up her mom’s grave the other day.//It must’ve been the day when–
Text.LocalizedString: Saw <NpcName>Lily</> cleaning up her mom’s grave the other day.//It must’ve been the day when–

Text.SourceString: It’s never easy to lose a parent… It wasn’t easy when I was little, and it isn’t easy now.//I feel for her and her brother.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s never easy to lose a parent… It wasn’t easy when I was little, and it isn’t easy now.//I feel for her and her brother.

Text.SourceString: It sure doesn’t sound like a bad idea to fly over Coral Island right now. Just when the leaves are changing color.
Text.LocalizedString: It sure doesn’t sound like a bad idea to fly over Coral Island right now. Just when the leaves are changing color.

Text.SourceString: Mama likes to be busy… I told <NpcName>Noah</> that it’s best to just let her.//It’s good for her to have activities so she doesn’t just sit around the house.
Text.LocalizedString: Mama likes to be busy… I told <NpcName>Noah</> that it’s best to just let her.//It’s good for her to have activities so she doesn’t just sit around the house.

Text.SourceString: Don’t always believe everything you hear around here, hon.//One time I heard a rumor from my own little brother about a ghost playing the piano in the community center. Yada yada yada.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t always believe everything you hear around here, hon.//One time I heard a rumor from my own little brother about a ghost playing the piano in the community center. Yada yada yada.

Text.SourceString: To have a ghost is one thing. Now they play the piano <Italic>too</>?//<portrait=angry>Where would they even learn to do such a thing?
Text.LocalizedString: To have a ghost is one thing. Now they play the piano <Italic>too</>?//<portrait=angry>Where would they even learn to do such a thing?

Text.SourceString: Oh hey, by the way… I like chatting with you, honey.//You’re smart. You know a lot of things, that’s for sure!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh hey, by the way… I like chatting with you, honey.//You’re smart. You know a lot of things, that’s for sure!

Text.SourceString: I like to eat the same things, especially for lunch.//It’s simple, you know? Eggplant lasagna or some hummus with <Italic>things</>. I just made a bunch of food and put it in the fridge.//<portrait=happy>It’s one less thing to think about in the morning.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to eat the same things, especially for lunch.//It’s simple, you know? Eggplant lasagna or some hummus with <Italic>things</>. I just made a bunch of food and put it in the fridge.//<portrait=happy>It’s one less thing to think about in the morning.

Text.SourceString: Miss the snow yet?
Text.LocalizedString: Miss the snow yet?

Text.SourceString: Whatever we bring to the Cherry Blossom Festival, please don’t let it be brussels sprouts. Yuck!
Text.LocalizedString: Whatever we bring to the Cherry Blossom Festival, please don’t let it be brussels sprouts. Yuck!

Text.SourceString: Blech! Sorry!
Text.LocalizedString: Blech! Sorry!

Text.SourceString: Bring on the snow! Winter’s here, so let’s get on with it. *laughs*
Text.LocalizedString: Bring on the snow! Winter’s here, so let’s get on with it. *laughs*

Text.SourceString: Spring is cool, but poor <NpcName>Char</>–//<portrait=happy>Ah! I’m just messing with you! Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: Spring is cool, but poor <NpcName>Char</>–//<portrait=happy>Ah! I’m just messing with you! Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: Gah! People here can get all over your business, right? Everyone keeps talking about poor <NpcName>Charles</> this, poor <NpcName>Charles</> that.//<portrait=concerned>Leave the man alone, people!
Text.LocalizedString: Gah! People here can get all over your business, right? Everyone keeps talking about poor <NpcName>Charles</> this, poor <NpcName>Charles</> that.//<portrait=concerned>Leave the man alone, people!

Text.SourceString: The trickiest part about being in basic training was the confinement. You gotta be okay with being with people in a small space for a long time.//<portrait=happy>Good thing I grew up with a lot of siblings. Trained since childhood, if you ask me!
Text.LocalizedString: The trickiest part about being in basic training was the confinement. You gotta be okay with being with people in a small space for a long time.//<portrait=happy>Good thing I grew up with a lot of siblings. Trained since childhood, if you ask me!

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to spending some time at the beach and soaking up the sun.//We should have a picnic at the beach, honey!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to spending some time at the beach and soaking up the sun.//We should have a picnic at the beach, honey!

Text.SourceString: We can swing by the house and invite Mama too.
Text.LocalizedString: We can swing by the house and invite Mama too.

Text.SourceString: Eggplant lasagna is far superior to generic lasagna.//The texture is out of this world!
Text.LocalizedString: Eggplant lasagna is far superior to generic lasagna.//The texture is out of this world!

Text.SourceString: It’s a little chilly today. It’s kinda nice.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a little chilly today. It’s kinda nice.

Text.SourceString: You know, this weather is perfect for some indoor stargazing. Just me, you, and a cozy blanket fort.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, this weather is perfect for some indoor stargazing. Just me, you, and a cozy blanket fort.

Text.SourceString: Rain on the roof reminds me of the sound of meteor showers against the spaceship.//Funny, huh? Makes me want to hold you closer.
Text.LocalizedString: Rain on the roof reminds me of the sound of meteor showers against the spaceship.//Funny, huh? Makes me want to hold you closer.

Text.SourceString: It’s a little chilly today. It’s kinda nice.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a little chilly today. It’s kinda nice.

Text.SourceString: Mama loves feeding the birds. She always has. When my brothers and I were kids, she taught us how to make bird feeders.//<portrait=happy>I still know how. I’ve just never done it.
Text.LocalizedString: Mama loves feeding the birds. She always has. When my brothers and I were kids, she taught us how to make bird feeders.//<portrait=happy>I still know how. I’ve just never done it.

Text.SourceString: My little brother and his friend, <NPCName>Alice</>, sure like talking about aliens. They have some…interesting theories.
Text.LocalizedString: My little brother and his friend, <NPCName>Alice</>, sure like talking about aliens. They have some…interesting theories.

Text.SourceString: The universe is big, so maybe we aren’t the only ones! Who knows?!
Text.LocalizedString: The universe is big, so maybe we aren’t the only ones! Who knows?!

Text.SourceString: I saw one of my brother’s cats on the roof the other day!//<portrait=normal>It was at Sam’s General Store.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw one of my brother’s cats on the roof the other day!//<portrait=normal>It was at Sam’s General Store.

Text.SourceString: Hopefully, with the rain this heavy, the sky will be clear by tomorrow night. It would be nice to stargaze, if you ask me.
Text.LocalizedString: Hopefully, with the rain this heavy, the sky will be clear by tomorrow night. It would be nice to stargaze, if you ask me.

Text.SourceString: I’m pretty sure my brother <NPCName>Frank</> will stick around on Coral Island. He and <NPCName>Erika</> have a life here.//<NPCName>Frank</> and <NPCName>Noah</>, yeah, they're set here.//I’m not sure about <NPCName>Eddy</>, though. I got the feeling he’s itching to see the world since he was a <Italic>baby</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m pretty sure my brother <NPCName>Frank</> will stick around on Coral Island. He and <NPCName>Erika</> have a life here.//<NPCName>Frank</> and <NPCName>Noah</>, yeah, they're set here.//I’m not sure about <NPCName>Eddy</>, though. I got the feeling he’s itching to see the world since he was a <Italic>baby</>.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Eddy</> is never going home for good.//Don't get me wrong, I'm happy for him. I just miss him sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Eddy</> is never going home for good.//Don't get me wrong, I'm happy for him. I just miss him sometimes.

Text.SourceString: Mama seems to be doing okay, without Dad.//For a while I was worried about her, but I’m not anymore.
Text.LocalizedString: Mama seems to be doing okay, without Dad.//For a while I was worried about her, but I’m not anymore.

Text.SourceString: Losing people we love is an inevitable part of getting older, huh?//It sucks, but we have to let go and keep living.
Text.LocalizedString: Losing people we love is an inevitable part of getting older, huh?//It sucks, but we have to let go and keep living.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Frank</> is so much like my dad, it hurts sometimes.//<portrait=happy>The other day he cracked a joke and it was like my old man was speaking through him from the other side. It was <Italic>something</>.//<portrait=normal>It’s funny how kids turn into their parents, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Frank</> is so much like my dad, it hurts sometimes.//<portrait=happy>The other day he cracked a joke and it was like my old man was speaking through him from the other side. It was <Italic>something</>.//<portrait=normal>It’s funny how kids turn into their parents, huh?

Text.SourceString: Gosh! Am I turning into my mom?!
Text.LocalizedString: Gosh! Am I turning into my mom?!

Text.SourceString: Thanks for always beliving in me, honey.//<portrait=normal>You're my rock.
Text.LocalizedString: Thanks for always beliving in me, honey.//<portrait=normal>You're my rock.

Text.SourceString: You're...wow you--//<portrait=blushing>You look incredible, <PlayerName>$Player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: You're...wow you--//<portrait=blushing>You look incredible, <PlayerName>$Player</>!

Text.SourceString: You smell amazing, honey!
Text.LocalizedString: You smell amazing, honey!

Text.SourceString: That's one of the things that I love about you.//You always smell so <Italic>yummy</>.
Text.LocalizedString: That's one of the things that I love about you.//You always smell so <Italic>yummy</>.

Text.SourceString: Hey you, cutie snowball.//<portrait=surprised>Oh no! I didn't mean to say that you <Italic>look</> like a snowball.//<portrait=sad>It was meant to be a compliment...and it's Winter...ugh.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey you, cutie snowball.//<portrait=surprised>Oh no! I didn't mean to say that you <Italic>look</> like a snowball.//<portrait=sad>It was meant to be a compliment...and it's Winter...ugh.

Text.SourceString: If it matters, I happen to <Italic>like</> snowball.
Text.LocalizedString: If it matters, I happen to <Italic>like</> snowball.

Text.SourceString: I got plenty of this pants in my closet.//I got them when I joined the military. They're free for grabs.
Text.LocalizedString: I got plenty of this pants in my closet.//I got them when I joined the military. They're free for grabs.

Text.SourceString: I should've asked for more. They're comfy and <Italic>really</> warm.
Text.LocalizedString: I should've asked for more. They're comfy and <Italic>really</> warm.

Text.SourceString: My brothers got me this sweater when I got accepted into the military.//<portrait=happy>It's my favorite sweater.
Text.LocalizedString: My brothers got me this sweater when I got accepted into the military.//<portrait=happy>It's my favorite sweater.

Text.SourceString: Being up there among the stars was like nothing I've ever experienced before.//It felt like I was part of something bigger than myself.
Text.LocalizedString: Being up there among the stars was like nothing I've ever experienced before.//It felt like I was part of something bigger than myself.

Text.SourceString: I remember looking out the window and seeing the Earth below me, and it just took my breath away.//<portrait=normal>It was so beautiful.
Text.LocalizedString: I remember looking out the window and seeing the Earth below me, and it just took my breath away.//<portrait=normal>It was so beautiful.

Text.SourceString: I always dreamed of being an astronaut, and now that I've been to space, I feel like I've accomplished everything I've ever wanted to.
Text.LocalizedString: I always dreamed of being an astronaut, and now that I've been to space, I feel like I've accomplished everything I've ever wanted to.

Text.SourceString: People always ask me what it's like to be in zero gravity, and it's hard to put into words.//<portrait=happy>It's like you're weightless, but at the same time, you feel like you're flying.
Text.LocalizedString: People always ask me what it's like to be in zero gravity, and it's hard to put into words.//<portrait=happy>It's like you're weightless, but at the same time, you feel like you're flying.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, when I'm having a bad day, I just close my eyes and think back to my time in space.//It reminds me that anything is possible if you work hard enough for it.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, when I'm having a bad day, I just close my eyes and think back to my time in space.//It reminds me that anything is possible if you work hard enough for it.

Text.SourceString: At every New Year's at Ama's house, we used to throw down and make dumplings as a family. And let me tell you, Ama had skills!//She was good at it. Ama knew how to whip up the best dumplings around.
Text.LocalizedString: At every New Year's at Ama's house, we used to throw down and make dumplings as a family. And let me tell you, Ama had skills!//She was good at it. Ama knew how to whip up the best dumplings around.

Text.SourceString: Ama is Mama's mom.
Text.LocalizedString: Ama is Mama's mom.

Text.SourceString: When Dad passed away, we covered all the mirrors in the house.//Good thing we don't have that many mirrors.
Text.LocalizedString: When Dad passed away, we covered all the mirrors in the house.//Good thing we don't have that many mirrors.

Text.SourceString: We moved the big mirror to my room, I never take them back out.//<portrait=concerned>Too lazy, I guess. Meh.
Text.LocalizedString: We moved the big mirror to my room, I never take them back out.//<portrait=concerned>Too lazy, I guess. Meh.

Text.SourceString: Always clean the house from top to bottom in Spring, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=happy>It's a way to get rid of any bad luck from the previous year and make room for good fortune.
Text.LocalizedString: Always clean the house from top to bottom in Spring, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=happy>It's a way to get rid of any bad luck from the previous year and make room for good fortune.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I feel like I don't fully fit in with either community, Dad's or my mom's...but then I remember that I don't have to choose.//<portrait=happy>I can be both.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I feel like I don't fully fit in with either community, Dad's or my mom's...but then I remember that I don't have to choose.//<portrait=happy>I can be both.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes people look at us funny when I call my mom, Mama.//I guess I don't look <Italic>too much</> like her.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes people look at us funny when I call my mom, Mama.//I guess I don't look <Italic>too much</> like her.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Eddy</>'s been a tech geek since he was a kid, always fiddling with electronics and computers.//<portrait=happy>So, it's not surprising that he's crushing it in coding now.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Eddy</>'s been a tech geek since he was a kid, always fiddling with electronics and computers.//<portrait=happy>So, it's not surprising that he's crushing it in coding now.

Text.SourceString: I feel like my dad is still with me every time I take off in a plane.//<portrait=happy>It's a comforting feeling, like he's watching over me.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel like my dad is still with me every time I take off in a plane.//<portrait=happy>It's a comforting feeling, like he's watching over me.

Text.SourceString: Hummus is my go-to snack. I could eat that stuff all day, every day.//Dip some carrots or pita chips in there, and it's a total game-changer.
Text.LocalizedString: Hummus is my go-to snack. I could eat that stuff all day, every day.//Dip some carrots or pita chips in there, and it's a total game-changer.

Text.SourceString: Kimchi and brussels sprouts? Bleh! No, thank you. They're like the two things I can't stand.//The smell alone is enough to make me run in the opposite direction.
Text.LocalizedString: Kimchi and brussels sprouts? Bleh! No, thank you. They're like the two things I can't stand.//The smell alone is enough to make me run in the opposite direction.

Text.SourceString: Eggplant lasagna is where it's at. It's so dang good, hearty and healthy at the same time.
Text.LocalizedString: Eggplant lasagna is where it's at. It's so dang good, hearty and healthy at the same time.

Text.SourceString: The tavern is legit the definition of community.//<portrait=normal>We got our regulars who've been with us since forever and always new faces to meet.
Text.LocalizedString: The tavern is legit the definition of community.//<portrait=normal>We got our regulars who've been with us since forever and always new faces to meet.

Text.SourceString: Working at the tavern has taught me some real-life skills. Like how to hustle and handle all sorts of characters.
Text.LocalizedString: Working at the tavern has taught me some real-life skills. Like how to hustle and handle all sorts of characters.

Text.SourceString: I'm all about trying new things. Life's too short to not take risks and step outside your comfort zone, ya know?//<portrait=annoyed>Except for <NpcName>Frank</>'s new recipes, yeah, nope.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm all about trying new things. Life's too short to not take risks and step outside your comfort zone, ya know?//<portrait=annoyed>Except for <NpcName>Frank</>'s new recipes, yeah, nope.

Text.SourceString: Aah...fresh start! Love Spring!
Text.LocalizedString: Aah...fresh start! Love Spring!

Text.SourceString: With Spring in full swing, I can finally ditch the bulky Winter coat and bust out my collection of freebies tees.//<portrait=normal>No more bundling up in layers.
Text.LocalizedString: With Spring in full swing, I can finally ditch the bulky Winter coat and bust out my collection of freebies tees.//<portrait=normal>No more bundling up in layers.

Text.SourceString: I can finally wear my shorts and tanks and let my skin breathe.
Text.LocalizedString: I can finally wear my shorts and tanks and let my skin breathe.

Text.SourceString: Everyone and their moms are trying to hit the beach and catch some sun.//<portrait=happy>It's way more crowded than Spring, but it's all good. More people, more fun.
Text.LocalizedString: Everyone and their moms are trying to hit the beach and catch some sun.//<portrait=happy>It's way more crowded than Spring, but it's all good. More people, more fun.

Text.SourceString: I sometime hit the beach with <NpcName>Chaem</>, and we play some mean volleyball.//Gotta stay active, ya know?
Text.LocalizedString: I sometime hit the beach with <NpcName>Chaem</>, and we play some mean volleyball.//Gotta stay active, ya know?

Text.SourceString: Fall is my favorite season, hands down.//<portrait=normal>The colors, the crisp air, it's all just so cozy and inviting.
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is my favorite season, hands down.//<portrait=normal>The colors, the crisp air, it's all just so cozy and inviting.

Text.SourceString: I think Fall might be <Italic>everyone</>'s favorite season.
Text.LocalizedString: I think Fall might be <Italic>everyone</>'s favorite season.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Erika</>'s my go-to girl for hair. Seriously, every dime I drop on her is totally worth it.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Erika</>'s my go-to girl for hair. Seriously, every dime I drop on her is totally worth it.

Text.SourceString: I'd kiss you but I'm all sweaty. Sorry!
Text.LocalizedString: I'd kiss you but I'm all sweaty. Sorry!

Text.SourceString: It's a constant battle to stay moisturized. Bah!//<portrait=concerned>Time to stock up on lip balm and lotion.
Text.LocalizedString: It's a constant battle to stay moisturized. Bah!//<portrait=concerned>Time to stock up on lip balm and lotion.

Text.SourceString: Honestly, I can't even remember the last time I had a proper sleep-in.//My body just wakes up on autopilot.
Text.LocalizedString: Honestly, I can't even remember the last time I had a proper sleep-in.//My body just wakes up on autopilot.

Text.SourceString: When it comes to coffee, I'm a bit of a snob. I can't stand anything that tastes burnt or watery.//<portrait=concerned>I'm no expert, but I can definitely tell when the coffee's bad.
Text.LocalizedString: When it comes to coffee, I'm a bit of a snob. I can't stand anything that tastes burnt or watery.//<portrait=concerned>I'm no expert, but I can definitely tell when the coffee's bad.

Text.SourceString: Everything's just so quiet and serene.
Text.LocalizedString: Everything's just so quiet and serene.

Text.SourceString: I hate having to wear so many layers.//It's like a workout just to get dressed in the morning!
Text.LocalizedString: I hate having to wear so many layers.//It's like a workout just to get dressed in the morning!

Text.SourceString: Since Dad's not in the picture anymore, my brothers and I gotta have each other's backs for Mama.
Text.LocalizedString: Since Dad's not in the picture anymore, my brothers and I gotta have each other's backs for Mama.

Text.SourceString: What's in this cleaning spray?//<portrait=annoyed>It smells so strong. This thing can kill <Italic>everything</>.
Text.LocalizedString: What's in this cleaning spray?//<portrait=annoyed>It smells so strong. This thing can kill <Italic>everything</>.

Text.SourceString: Sorry, <PlayerName>$Player</>, you're kind of on the way. Gotta clean these up.//If you need to order, talk to <NpcName>Frank</> over there.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry, <PlayerName>$Player</>, you're kind of on the way. Gotta clean these up.//If you need to order, talk to <NpcName>Frank</> over there.

Text.SourceString: I made this special dish just for you.//I hope it gives you energy today.
Text.LocalizedString: I made this special dish just for you.//I hope it gives you energy today.

Text.SourceString: I wanted to surprise you with something delicious, so I prepared this homemade meal.
Text.LocalizedString: I wanted to surprise you with something delicious, so I prepared this homemade meal.

Text.SourceString: I can't believe we're married! So cool!
Text.LocalizedString: I can't believe we're married! So cool!
